{% extends "base.html.twig" %}

{% block title %}How It Works — Minoo{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <div class="content-section flow-lg">
    <div>
      <h1>How Minoo Works</h1>
      <p class="text-secondary">Minoo's Elder Support Program connects Elders with volunteers through a simple, coordinator-supported process.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="flow">
      <h2>For Elders Needing Help</h2>
      <ol class="how-it-works__list">
        <li><strong>Submit a request</strong> — Tell us what you need: a ride, help with groceries, yard work, or a friendly visit. You can submit online or have someone submit on your behalf.</li>
        <li><strong>A coordinator reviews your request</strong> — A community coordinator in your area looks at your request and finds an available volunteer nearby.</li>
        <li><strong>A volunteer reaches out</strong> — The matched volunteer contacts you at the phone number you provided to arrange the details.</li>
        <li><strong>Follow-up</strong> — After the visit, the coordinator checks in to make sure everything went well.</li>
      </ol>
      <p><a href="/elders" class="btn btn--primary">Request Help</a></p>
    </section>

    <section class="flow">
      <h2>For Volunteers</h2>
      <ol class="how-it-works__list">
        <li><strong>Sign up</strong> — Share your name, phone number, availability, and the types of help you can offer.</li>
        <li><strong>Get matched</strong> — A coordinator assigns you to requests that fit your location and availability.</li>
        <li><strong>Provide support</strong> — Connect with the Elder, arrange the details, and help out.</li>
        <li><strong>Mark complete</strong> — Let the coordinator know when the visit is done.</li>
      </ol>
      <p><a href="/volunteer" class="btn btn--secondary">Volunteer</a></p>
    </section>

    <section class="flow">
      <h2>Requesting on Behalf of an Elder</h2>
      <p>Family members, friends, or community workers can submit requests on behalf of an Elder. When doing so:</p>
      <ul class="how-it-works__list">
        <li>Check the "I'm requesting on behalf of an Elder" box on the request form</li>
        <li>Provide the Elder's name</li>
        <li>Confirm that the Elder has given permission for the request</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This ensures the Elder knows about and consents to receiving volunteer support.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="flow">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="flow">
        <div>
          <h3>Is there a cost?</h3>
          <p>No. Minoo is a free community service.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>How are volunteers screened?</h3>
          <p>Volunteers are matched through community coordinators who know the area and the people involved.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>What if I need help urgently?</h3>
          <p>Minoo is for non-emergency support. For emergencies, call 911. For urgent community needs, contact your band office or local social services.</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3>Can I cancel a request?</h3>
          <p>Yes. Contact your coordinator or log in to your dashboard to update your request.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
